narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Throughout this semester there was *no* contact with people with other advisers. There should have been some sort of class-wide presentation day towards the end where everyone gave their spiel. Otherwise, this semester was a lot of fun. Working on a project without much interference is always good.
More direction on projects - there was no faculty guidance and no support at all

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you see this, it's too late, and you already committed to 410+411. Know that you can drop out midway through the sequence if you want to -- they can't do anything to you.
If you took the first semester of the course, you need to take this one. If you like your paper/project topic, it'll be fine (and maybe even enjoyable).
No. 410 and 411 were a waste of two CS credits
